The paper discusses the design of fair predictors in a supervised learning setting, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses the issue of discrimination, which is related to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the use of an auxiliary variable for prediction is a statistical inference technique, which is relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI).
